                            <comment id="14473458" author="werdna" created="Mon, 26 Nov 2012 13:00:51 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Proposed solution:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ol&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;add new field to &lt;tt&gt;MapStyleConstructorCall&lt;/tt&gt; that contains the original &lt;tt&gt;ConstructorCallExpression&lt;/tt&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;set the sloc of the &lt;tt&gt;MapStyleConstructorCall&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;in &lt;tt&gt;MapStyleConstructorCall.visit(GroovyCodeVisitor)&lt;/tt&gt;, do something like the following:&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;


&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;        @Override
        &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;public&lt;/span&gt; void visit(&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;final&lt;/span&gt; GroovyCodeVisitor visitor) {
            &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (visitor &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;instanceof&lt;/span&gt; AsmClassGenerator) {
                acg = (AsmClassGenerator) visitor;
            } &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;else&lt;/span&gt; {
                originalConsCallExpr.visit(visitor);
            } 
            &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;super&lt;/span&gt;.visit(visitor);
        }
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This would probably work for Groovy-Eclipse, but I have not tried to actually implement this.  Do you see any problems with this in using this for Groovy?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14473435" author="melix" created="Tue, 27 Nov 2012 13:13:14 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The change is ok for Groovy. Just let me know if it&apos;s ok for Eclipse too and I&apos;ll push the change.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14473566" author="werdna" created="Tue, 27 Nov 2012 18:53:01 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks.  Pull request is here:&lt;/p&gt;

